{"title_page": "Canna (gamer)", "text_new": "{{Korean name|[[Kim (Korean name)|Kim]]}}\n{{Infobox video game player|ID=Canna|name=\uae40\ucc3d\ub3d9|name_trans=Kim Chang-dong|image=|caption=|status=Active|birth_date={{birth date and age|2000|02|11}}|birth_place=[[South Korea]]|nationality=South Korean|earnings=|games=''[[League of Legends]]''|role=Top Laner|years1=2019\u2013present|team1=[[T1 (esports)|T1]]|highlights=*1\u00d7 [[League of Legends Champions Korea|LCK]] champion}}\n\n'''Kim Chang-dong''' ({{lang-ko|\uae40\ucc3d\ub3d9}}; born February 11, 2000), better known by his in-game name '''Canna''' ({{lang-ko|\uce78\ub098}}), is a [[South Korea]]n professional ''[[League of Legends]]'' player. He is a top laner player who currently plays for [[T1 (esports)|T1]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=442&aid=0000109686|title=[\uc624\ud53c\uc15c] '\ub85c\uce58' \uae40\uac15\ud76c T1 \ud569\ub958... '\uad6c\ub9c8\uc720\uc2dc' \uc774\ubbfc\ud615 \ub4f1 \uc5f0\uc2b5\uc0dd 1\uad70 \uc2b9\uaca9|website=sports.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref> He made his debut on KeSPA Cup 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=442&aid=0000111352|title=[KeSPA \ucef5] \"\ub370\ubdd4\uc804 \uc544\uc26c\uc6cc... \ub2e4\uc74c \uacbd\uae30\ub294 \uacf5\uaca9\uc801\uc73c\ub85c \ud50c\ub808\uc774\ud560 \uac83\" T1 '\uce78\ub098' \uae40\ucc3d\ub3d9|website=sports.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref>\n\nHe was a trainee of T1 before being promoted to the team.\n\n== Early life ==\nCanna was born on February 11, 2000. His hometown is in [[Andong|Andong City]].\n\nHis role model is Khan.<ref>{{Citation|title=Canna on becoming T1's new top laner, following his idol Khan {{!}} Ashley Kang|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qDu574qBxmg|language=en|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref>\n\nHis in-game name was based on his favourite anime character, Kanna Kamui, from [[Miss Kobayashi's Dragon Maid]].<ref>{{Citation|title=T1 Canna on being compared to Impact and Duke, which anime his IGN is based in {{!}} Ashley Kang|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZFtrI9VF_rI|language=en|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Season 9 ===\nDuring his time as trainee, he and four other trainees from T1, including Ellim, Mask, Gumayushi and Kuri had competed in the 2019 LoL Amateur Tournament. The team was called 'T1 rookies', and they had successfully won the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://vod.afreecatv.com/PLAYER/STATION/44318149&szFrom=naver|title=[\uad11\uc8fc\ubc14\uc704\uac8c vs T1 rookies] 2019 LoL \uc544\ub9c8\ucd94\uc5b4 \ub300\ud68c \uacb0\uc2b9\uc804 1\uc138\ud2b8|website=AfreecaTV|language=en|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://vod.afreecatv.com/PLAYER/STATION/44319590|title=[\uad11\uc8fc\ubc14\uc704\uac8c vs T1 rookies] 2019 LoL \uc544\ub9c8\ucd94\uc5b4 \ub300\ud68c \uacb0\uc2b9\uc804 2\uc138\ud2b8|website=AfreecaTV|language=en|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref>\n\nOn November 26, 2019, T1 announced that Canna will be joining as part of the roster.<ref name=\":0\" /> His first game after the announcement was against Gen.G during KeSPA Cup 2019, and his first champion used was Aatrox, which he won.\n\n=== Season 10 ===\nHe played his first LCK game on February 7, 2020, against Hanwha Life Esports.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=236&aid=0000199418|title=[LCK] \ud55c\ud654\uc0dd\uba85\uc5d0 1\uc138\ud2b8 \ub0b4\uc900 T1, '\uce78\ub098' \uae40\ucc3d\ub3d9 \uad50\uccb4 \ud22c\uc785|website=sports.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref> He and his team finished the split at second place, which qualified them to the second round of playoffs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=236&aid=0000201480|title=[LCK] \"\ub561\ud050, APK\" T1, \ub4dc\ub798\uace4X 2\uc138\ud2b8 \ud328\ubc30\ub85c 2\uc704 \ud655\uc815|website=sports.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref>\n\nOn April 25, 2020, he and his team successfully won the LCK Spring finals. This was his first LCK title, which made him a 'Royal Roader{{ref|1|a}}'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=347&aid=0000142622|title=T1 '\uce78\ub098' \uae40\ucc3d\ub3d9, \ub85c\uc5f4 \ub85c\ub354 \ub4f1\uadf9|website=sports.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-26}}</ref>\n\n== Accomplishments ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Team\n!Event\n!Place\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2020\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[T1 (esports)|T1]]\n|KeSPA Cup 2019\n| style=\"background:#c96;\" |3rd\u20134th\n|-\n|''League of Legends'' Champions Korea Spring 2020\n| style=\"background:gold;\" |1st\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== Notes ==\n1. {{note|1|a}}A Korean term given to the rookies that win the championship in their first year.\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{Twitch|id=canna}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:South Korean esports players]]\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:SK Telecom T1 players]]\n[[Category:Top laners]]\n[[Category:Twitch streamers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Korean name|[[Kim (Korean name)|Kim]]}}\n{{Infobox video game player|ID=Canna|name=\uae40\ucc3d\ub3d9|name_trans=Kim Chang-dong|image=|caption=|status=Active|birth_date={{birth date and age|2000|02|11}}|birth_place=[[South Korea]]|nationality=South Korean|earnings=|games=''[[League of Legends]]''|role=Top Laner|years1=2019\u2013present|team1=[[T1|T1 (esports)]]|highlights=*1\u00d7 [[League of Legends Champions Korea|LCK]] champion}}\n\n'''Kim Chang-dong''' ({{lang-ko|\uae40\ucc3d\ub3d9}}; born February 11, 2000), better known by his in-game name '''Canna''' ({{lang-ko|\uce78\ub098}}), is a [[South Korea]]n professional ''[[League of Legends]]'' player. He is a top laner player who currently plays for [[T1 (esports)|T1]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=442&aid=0000109686|title=[\uc624\ud53c\uc15c] '\ub85c\uce58' \uae40\uac15\